==English==

===Etymology===
From genos (Greek for family, tribe or race) and -cide (Latin - occidere, to massacre)

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|[[RP]] /ˈdʒenəsaɪd/}}

===Noun===
'''genocide'''
# A form of violent [[social]] [[conflict]] or [[war]] in which armed power organizations aim to [[systematic]]ally destroy [[ethnic]] or [[national]] groups.

